<div class="comment-wrapper"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/dd033b3ed46d65c7d7394eab52d53e6b?s=50"></div><header><strong>Source vs Sources</strong> from <string>Evan Maloney</string> &lt;emaloney at gilt.com&gt;<p>December 18, 2015 at 09:00:00am</p></header><div class="content"><p>What is the preferred canonical directory name for Swift source code?<br></p><p>&quot;Source&quot; sounds right to my ear because it&#39;s short for &quot;source code&quot;.<br></p><p>However, &quot;Sources&quot; seems to be in more common usage, at least at Apple and in the current examples/documentation for SPM.<br></p><p>I&#39;d rather adopt something more likely to be in common usage than go with something where the lack of the trailing &quot;s&quot; is going to be a long-term source of mental toe-stubbing.<br></p><p>Any guidance appreciated!<br></p><p>Thanks,<br>E.<br></p></div><ul class="comments"><li class="comment"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ae51ca494b37cc270597830da66f089f?s=50"></div><header><strong>Source vs Sources</strong> from <string>Max Howell</string> &lt;max.howell at apple.com&gt;<p>December 18, 2015 at 11:00:00am</p></header><div class="content"><p>We encourage “Sources”, but all of “src”, “srcs”, “Source” and “Sources” are fully supported.<br></p><p>&gt; On Dec 18, 2015, at 8:57 AM, Evan Maloney via swift-build-dev &lt;swift-build-dev at swift.org&gt; wrote:<br>&gt; <br>&gt; What is the preferred canonical directory name for Swift source code?<br>&gt; <br>&gt; &quot;Source&quot; sounds right to my ear because it&#39;s short for &quot;source code&quot;.<br>&gt; <br>&gt; However, &quot;Sources&quot; seems to be in more common usage, at least at Apple and in the current examples/documentation for SPM.<br>&gt; <br>&gt; I&#39;d rather adopt something more likely to be in common usage than go with something where the lack of the trailing &quot;s&quot; is going to be a l